The paper deals with the linear complexity of a binary sequence generated from Legendre polynomial quotients, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The authors also use mathematical tools such as modular arithmetic and polynomial algebra, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the Legendre symbol is a concept from number theory (cs.NT), which further supports the inclusion of this paper in these sub-categories.
